explanation:
OS_CHECK_POINTER: Macro may perform validation and early return or abort; required to know if subsequent statements can be skipped (affects control flow and whether any code is dead).
memset: Initializes *bin_prop; needed to determine whether the subsequent strncpy/assignment are redundant (possible dead initialization vs required behavior).
strncpy: Copies record->name_entry into bin_prop->name; needed to know if this produces observable effects (e.g., truncation/termination) and therefore not dead.
OS_ObjectIdGetById: Determines whether the branch body executes (sets return_code and token); its return semantics control reachability of the code inside the if and thus whether that code could be dead.
OS_LOCK_MODE_GLOBAL, LOCAL_OBJID_TYPE: Constants/enum values passed to OS_ObjectIdGetById that may affect its behavior and thus whether the if-body executes.
osal_id_t: Type of sem_id; required to reason about validity/representation of the identifier and any caller-visible effects.
OS_object_token_t: Type of token filled by OS_ObjectIdGetById and passed to subsequent functions; needed to reason about side-effects and whether use of token is meaningful.
OS_common_record_t: Structure type of record; required to confirm that accessing record->name_entry and record->creator is valid and has observable effects (not padding/unused fields).
OS_OBJECT_TABLE_GET: Macro/function used to obtain record from OS_global_bin_sem_table and token; needed to know whether this access has side-effects or can be elided.
OS_global_bin_sem_table: Global table used by OS_OBJECT_TABLE_GET; the contents determine the source of data copied into bin_prop and whether the copy is meaningful.
OS_bin_sem_prop_t: Type of bin_prop; required to determine which fields are initialized/modified and whether those writes are observable (i.e., not dead).
OS_BinSemGetInfo_Impl: Called inside the if; may perform additional observable actions or update bin_prop/return_code — needed to determine if prior operations are necessary or could be dead.
OS_ObjectIdRelease: Releases the token; required to know if the release has observable effects (resource accounting, side-effects) and so whether the call is essential.
OS_SUCCESS: Return code constant compared to return value of OS_ObjectIdGetById; needed to determine which branch is taken and thus which statements could be dead.
